docs:

#### docsheader ####
text: Invite a member
----
ref: invite
#### docsstep ####
step: 1
----
text: Go to [**Members**](../#manage) tab in your community and, click on the green **Invite** button.
----
image: button.png
#### docsstep ####
step: 2
----
text: Search for a user by entering their name, affiliation or email address.

*Note:* Only users with public [profile visibility](../../../profile/changing-profile-visibility/) are searchable and only users with public email visibility are searchable by their email address.
----
image: invite-dialog.png
#### docsstep ####
step: 3
----
text: Select a user from the list by using the arrow up/down keys and pressing enter to select. Note, you can select multiple people from the list. Once, select they will appear in the area above the search field.
----
image: select.png
#### docsstep ####
step: 4
----
text: Choose a **role** for all selected users. The chosen role is applied to all users. You can provide an **optional message** to the invited users.
----
image: role.png
#### docsstep ####
step: 5
----
text: Click the blue **Invite** button. Each invited user will receive an email notification, and be able to see the invitation under [My requests](../../../get-started/navigating-zenodo/#dashboard).
----
image: invite.png
